The first part of the course is devoted to Soviet history, its periods and their specific features.
Then the chronological sketches of the development of different arts follow. The basic part of the course is devoted to the analysis of different artificial texts of the epoch (incl. translations of literary texts, films, paintings, etc.).Objectives/eesmärkid:  The purpose of course is to give a picture of development of the culture of the Soviet era (both "Socialist realism" and its independent opponents). The cultural history of pre-Stalin, Stalin and post-Stalin periods will be taken in the connection with political struggle inside the communist party, social development of the country and mechanisms of the state control. The literature, art, cinema, music, theater, popular culture, architecture in the USSR will be discussed. Underground culture and civil-right activism are the subjects of the course also.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  After completing the course the student 1) gets acquainted with a historical context of the Soviet era; 2) knows about a cultural life of the USSR (Russian, first of all) in the epoch; 3) receives the general concept about the main trends of Soviet music, film, art and literature; 4) understands cultural, social and political context of Socialist realism and (post) avant-garde.
